  "text": "There is a growing recognition that news and social media channels can be exploited to shape individual views through evidence and misinformation. While the value of news and social media as a population intervention to positively influence health behaviors has been examined [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , the impact that socially-shaped misinformation has on decision-making and health outcomes is an emerging concern. We explored a healthcare decision that appears susceptible to influence of news and social media-the choice of administering the human papillomavirus (HPV) vaccine to an adolescent.",
